The productivity measures the rate of a CO2 separation process and may be evaluated by dividing ΔDICflow,3→1, i.e., 0.17 M, by the sum of the absorption time and the desorption time. The CO2 absorption and desorption processes took 1.6 and 0.4 h, respectively, leading to a productivity of 0.085 M h−1 or 8.5 ×\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
